  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nIn these instructions https://chainsafe.github.io/lodestar/usage/local/, the command that's shown uses command  `--chain.genesisStateFile ./dev/genesis.ssz`, where the path of that file is relative to the root directory that you define with option `--rootDir`  (which is `./.lodestar` by default).\r\n\r\nWhen you clone the latest 'master' branch and run `yarn run cli dev --help` it shows \r\n```\r\nCommand used to quickly bootstrap beacon node and validators\r\n\r\ndev\r\n  ...\r\n\r\nOptions:\r\n  ...\r\n  --undefined                   Genesis state in ssz-encoded format   [string]\r\n```\r\n\r\nNotice how it's missing the following, and just shows it as `--undefined` in the Options section, whereas I think it should instead be shown as a Command as shown below\r\n```\r\nchain\r\n  --chain.genesisStateFile\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\n```\r\nchain\r\n  --chain.genesisStateFile    Genesis state file in ssz-encoded format. File location relative to Lodestar root directory.        [string] [ default: \"\" ]\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Steps to Reproduce**\r\n\r\n1. Clone the latest Lodestart repo `git clone https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar`\r\n2. Switch to a version of Node.js that's later than v12 (requirement of package.json) e.g. `nvm use 14.4.0`\r\n3. Build from source `yarn install; yarn run build`\r\n4. View CLI dev help `yarn run cli dev --help`\r\n5. See error\r\n\r\n**Desktop (please complete the following information):**\r\n - OS: macOS Mojave 10.14.6\r\n - Version:\r\n```\r\n$ yarn run cli --version\r\n0.9.0\r\n```\r\n - Branch: master\r\n - Commit hash: 26a935ce7973c95d58570ef55c71ebc8a18bb61b\r\n",
